doc.after: Most Swiss German dialects have rounded front vowels unlike other High German dialects 7 Only in the Low Alemannic dialects of northwest Switzerland mainly Basel and in the Walliser dialects have the rounded front vowels been unrounded In Basel the rounding is being reintroduced under the influence of other Swiss German dialects
